      <item>
        <title>LKRG &amp; security-misc questions</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[disrupt_the_flow]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>Yes. I use security-misc on ParrotOS which is a Debian based distribution and it runs with no problems. The experimental options might introduce some minor issues like not being able to re-log in after logging out. security-misc can be installed as explained here <a href="https://www.whonix.org/wiki/Security-misc#install" rel="nofollow noopener">https://www.whonix.org/wiki/Security-misc#install</a>. LKRG can be installed in Ubuntu as explained here <a href="https://www.whonix.org/wiki/Linux_Kernel_Runtime_Guard_LKRG#Installation" rel="nofollow noopener">https://www.whonix.org/wiki/Linux_Kernel_Runtime_Guard_LKRG#Installation</a>. Be aware that in my ParrotOS that uses the latest Stable Linux Kernel LKRG won’t run. I haven’t looked into it so I don’t know why. Also having LKRG installed on your host OS and trying to run Whonix or other VMs in Virtualbox may lead to this bug <a href="https://www.openwall.com/lists/lkrg-users/2019/11/18/1" rel="nofollow noopener">https://www.openwall.com/lists/lkrg-users/2019/11/18/1</a>. It will run in VMs though. If you mean Whonix as host OS not atm. Look here <a href="https://www.whonix.org/wiki/Whonix-Host" rel="nofollow noopener">https://www.whonix.org/wiki/Whonix-Host</a> and <a href="https://forums.whonix.org/t/whonix-host-operating-system/3931" class="inline-onebox">Whonix host operating system</a><br>
Also check this to see what packages are safe to be installed on Debian hosts <a href="https://www.whonix.org/wiki/Whonix_Packages_for_Debian_Hosts" rel="nofollow noopener">https://www.whonix.org/wiki/Whonix_Packages_for_Debian_Hosts</a></p>
          <p><a href="http://forums.whonix.org/t/lkrg-security-misc-questions/10528/2">Read full topic</a></p>
        ]]></description>
